---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Lexicon | Grithos"
  description="The language of Grithos — key terms defined. From Grithosian to Forge Day, every word carries weight. Learn the vocabulary of a philosophy built on grit and ethos."
  ogTitle="The Lexicon — Grithos"
  ogDescription="The language of Grithos defined. Every word carries weight. Learn the vocabulary of a philosophy built on grit and ethos."
  ogUrl="https://grithos.com/lexicon"
  canonical="https://grithos.com/lexicon"
  activePage="lexicon"
>

<style is:inline>
  /* ═══ PAGE HERO ═══ */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 160px 0 80px;
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 40%; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 800px; height: 800px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(201,147,90,.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .page-hero .wrap { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .page-hero-overline {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .page-hero-title {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 52px);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .page-hero-sub {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 18px);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ═══ LEXICON ═══ */
  .lexicon-section {
    padding: 0 0 120px;
  }
  .lexicon-list {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .lexicon-item {
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .lexicon-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .lexicon-term {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.5vw, 26px);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .lexicon-pronunciation {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--gold);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .lexicon-def {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.85;
  }
  .lexicon-def em {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 14px;
    display: block;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }
  .lexicon-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    background: var(--gold-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--gold-border);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  /* ═══ CLOSING ═══ */
  .closing {
    padding: 0 0 120px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .closing-divider {
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 80px;
  }
  .closing-text {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.8vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 20px;
  }
  .closing-sub {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 18px);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 480px;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
  }
  .back-link {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    transition: color .2s;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .back-link svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; }
</style>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="page-hero-overline reveal d1">The Language</p>
    <h1 class="page-hero-title reveal d2">The Lexicon</h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub reveal d3">Every philosophy has its language. These are the words that carry weight in Grithos.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LEXICON -->
<section class="lexicon-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="lexicon-list">

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Grithos</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ˈɡrɪθ.ɒs/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">A philosophy of life built on grit and ethos. The fusion of relentless endurance and moral character. Not a religion. Not a movement. A way of living.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Grithosian</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ɡrɪˈθoʊ.zi.ən/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">A person who lives by the philosophy of Grithos. Not someone who merely studies it — someone who practices it. Daily. A Grithosian tells the truth, keeps their word, owns what is theirs, and builds what lasts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Four Pillars</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Structure</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The foundational categories of Grithos: <strong>Truth, Strength, Discipline,</strong> and <strong>Legacy.</strong> Every tenet, every practice, every decision filters through one of these four pillars.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d4">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Twelve Tenets</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Structure</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">Twelve rules of life — three under each pillar. They are not suggestions. They are the operating instructions for a Grithosian life. Memorized. Practiced. Lived.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Creed</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Foundation</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The central declaration of Grithos. Five lines. No filler. It defines what a Grithosian believes about truth, strength, ownership, mortality, and legacy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Bounds</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/baʊndz/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The natural laws, limits, and structures that govern reality. Gravity. Time. Consequence. A Grithosian does not fight the bounds — a Grithosian trusts them, works within them, and builds accordingly. <em>"Trust the Bounds." — Tenet IX</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Lineage</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Heritage</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The historical and philosophical figures whose lives embodied the principles of Grithos before it had a name. Not founders, but proof that these ideas have always existed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d4">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Forge Day</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">March 13</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The founding date of Grithos — Friday the 13th. A day the superstitious fear. A day Grithos was forged in. On Forge Day, do one thing that is hard on purpose. Every year. No exceptions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Daily Practice</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">365 Days</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">One practice per day, every day of the year. Each tied to a tenet. Each tied to a pillar. Philosophy without practice is just talk. The Daily Practice is where Grithos becomes real.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Redirect</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ˌriː.dɪˈrɛkt/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The act of immediately pivoting when something fails, falls through, or changes. No spiraling. No stewing. No standing at closed doors. Something broke? Redirect. Now. <em>"Redirect Immediately." — Tenet VIII</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Own It</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The Grithos posture toward everything — results, failures, decisions, and outcomes. A Grithosian does not blame. A Grithosian does not deflect. Whatever happened, own your piece of it. Then move.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d4">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Mark</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The legacy a Grithosian leaves behind. Not fame. Not wealth. The mark — the evidence that you lived with purpose, built something that outlasted you, and left the world different because you were in it. <em>"Not a scratch — a mark." — Tenet XII</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Grit</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ɡrɪt/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The half of Grithos that endures. Relentless persistence. The refusal to quit when it gets hard. Not stubbornness — directed force. Grit without ethos is just aggression. Together, they become Grithos.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Ethos</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ˈiː.θɒs/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The half of Grithos that guides. Moral character. The internal compass that says do right — even when it costs you. Ethos without grit is just philosophy. Together, they become Grithos.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CLOSING -->
<section class="closing">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="closing-divider"></div>
    <p class="closing-text reveal d1">Learn the language. Live the philosophy.</p>
    <p class="closing-sub reveal d2">Words mean nothing without action behind them.</p>
    <div class="reveal d3">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18" /></svg>
        Back to Grithos
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
